From: Lukas Stockner <lukas@lukasstockner.de>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 20:11:04 +0200
Subject: ipq806x: add CONFIG_GPIO_WATCHDOG

The AP-325 (and variants) has an external watchdog, so this is needed to
regularly toggle the GPIO and keep the watchdog happy.

Signed-off-by: Lukas Stockner <lukas@lukasstockner.de>

diff --git a/target/linux/ipq806x/config-6.12 b/target/linux/ipq806x/config-6.12
index 6ade610d56a3440afbf24166d7657e5706bc95bc..954e5b063a246ab597de49d22837f4ad1811805d 100644
--- a/target/linux/ipq806x/config-6.12
+++ b/target/linux/ipq806x/config-6.12
@@ -186,6 +186,8 @@ CONFIG_GENERIC_VDSO_32=y
 CONFIG_GLOB=y
 CONFIG_GPIOLIB_IRQCHIP=y
 CONFIG_GPIO_CDEV=y
+CONFIG_GPIO_WATCHDOG=y
+CONFIG_GPIO_WATCHDOG_ARCH_INITCALL=y
 CONFIG_GRO_CELLS=y
 CONFIG_HARDEN_BRANCH_PREDICTOR=y
 CONFIG_HARDIRQS_SW_RESEND=y
